notesStmt.note: An anonymous entry, dated 8 Adar 5680 (1708): inscribed, folio 188r.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: A festival prayer book, according to the rite of Algiers.

msItem.title: Services for the week of the 4th of Marḥeshvan

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 4; ruled lines: 22; written lines: 22; Uniform layout. Initial words written in larger characters. Leaf catchwords on every verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Sefardi (North African) semi-cursive script, of the 17th century.

binding.p: Post-1600. Brown leather, blind tooled. Boxed. Spine: 'Machazor. Secundum Ritum Algerensum. Hebraice. Mus. Brit. Jure Emptionis. 19,780.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: M. Aschkenazi: purchased from him by the British Museum through D. Nutt on 08 April 1854: inscribed, folio [189v].
